com.myscript.atk.itc

Class SmartWord

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.myscript.atk.itc.SmartWord

  • public class SmartWord
extends Object
    A SmartWord is an abstraction of a real word interpreted by Interactive Text Component
    It presents the different methods available on a word.

      • getCharDisplayInfoList

        public List<SmartWordCharDisplayInfo> getCharDisplayInfoList()
        Gives the list of SmartWord characters information necessary to display
        SamrtWord characters one by one.


        Part of the typeset feature. It should be used when drawing each
        typesetted character of a word one by one. This API
        will be of no use when drawing a typesetted SmartWord from its full selected
        candidate label string

        Returns:
        The list of necessary information to display internally computed
        SmartWord character boxes.

      • getReshapedChars

        public List<Char> getReshapedChars()
        Gives the list of reshaped SmartWord characters. It corresponds to the representation
        of the characters with contextual representation (ligature case for example).


        Part of the typeset feature. It should be used when typesetting
        feature is drawing character of the word one by one. Indeed when drawing a
        typeseted SmartWord from its full selected candidate label string this API
        will be of no use.

        Returns:
        The list of reshaped SmartWord typeset characters to be used at display time.

      • getDisplayFrame

        public Rect getDisplayFrame()
        Gives the typeset SmartWord selected candidate label display frame.


        Part of the typeset feature. It should be used when typesetting
        feature is drawing character of the word one by one. Indeed when drawing a
        typeseted SmartWord from its full selected candidate label string this API
        will be of no use.

        Returns:
        The computed display frame.
